  "body": "Config states that mocha options can be passed through hardhat.config.js like so...\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nexport default {\r\n  solidity: '0.8.6',\r\n  mocha: {\r\n    file: 'test/hooks.ts',\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\ntest/hooks.ts may contain something like:\r\n```ts\r\nafterEach(async () => {\r\n  // do cleanup task\r\n  console.log('running cleanup!')\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis works if we run the entire test suite ex:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ hardhat test\r\n\r\n  MyContract\r\n    someFunction()\r\n      ✓ Should ... whatever (83ms)\r\nrunning cleanup!\r\n      ✓ Should ... whatever 2 (64ms)\r\nrunning cleanup!\r\n```\r\n\r\nhowever, it _ignores_ the hooks file if we test an individual file like so...\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ hardhat test ./test/MyContract.test.ts\r\n\r\n  MyContract\r\n    someFunction()\r\n      ✓ Should ... whatever (83ms)\r\n      ✓ Should ... whatever 2 (64ms)\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe this is an issue with mocha instead?",
